com.amplifyframework.api.rest

Interface RestBehavior

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApiCategoryBehavior
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApiCategory, ApiPlugin, AWSApiPlugin

    public interface RestBehavior
    REST behaviors which include the family of HTTP verbs (GET, POST, etc.).

    • Method Detail

      • get

        RestOperation get(RestOptions request,
                  Consumer<RestResponse> onResponse,
                  Consumer<ApiException> onFailure)
        This is a helper method for easily invoking GET HTTP request. Requires that only one API is configured in your `amplifyconfiguration.json`. Otherwise, emits an ApiException to the provided `onFailure` callback.
        Parameters:
        request - GET request object.
        onResponse - Invoked when a response is available from the REST endpoint. A response may contain a non-200 error code from the endpoint.
        onFailure - Invoked upon failure to obtain a response from the REST endpoint
        Returns:
        An ApiOperation to track progress and provide a means to cancel the asynchronous operation
